# Git workflow — kitchen library

- Work on a **feature branch** (e.g. `improvement/short-description`). Do not commit large features directly to `main` without review and local checks.
- After each meaningful change, **verify in a browser** (static server from repo root): affected pages load, modals work, search still works.
- Use **Conventional Commits**: `feat(html):`, `fix(riviera):`, `chore(cursor):`, `docs:`.
- **Commit often** with small, logical messages; **push the branch regularly** for backup.
- Merge to `main` only when smoke tests pass on your machine.
